Spider protects your privacy on the internet by hiding the connection
between your Internet address and the services you use. We believe Spider
is reasonably secure, but please ensure you read the instructions and
configure it properly.

To build Spider from source:
        ./configure && make && make install

To build Spider from a just-cloned git reposispidery:
        sh autogen.sh && ./configure && make && make install

Home page:
        https://www.spiderproject.org/

Download new versions:
        https://www.spiderproject.org/download/download.html

Documentation, including links to installation and setup instructions:
        https://www.spiderproject.org/docs/documentation.html

Making applications work with Spider:
        https://wiki.spiderproject.org/projects/spider/wiki/doc/SpiderifyHOWTO

Frequently Asked Questions:
        https://www.spiderproject.org/docs/faq.html


To get started working on Spider development:
        See the doc/HACKING directory.
